Remove NA values

Source: R/na_drop.R
na.drop.Rd

Removes missing values from a dataset.

Usage

na.drop(xin)

Arguments

xin

A numeric vector.

Value

A vector without missing values

Author

Richard Murray Lark <murray.lark@nottingham.ac.uk>

Examples

x<-evapotranspiration$`ET(mm)`
na.drop(x)
